        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What makes someone an academic or a scholar?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What qualifies a distinguished savant?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Is it making the grade? Getting the degree? Publishing the journal?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Getting picked?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Or is it merely the insatiable desire to learn and to grow? And the ability—the tenacity—to make that learning happen?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Outside ivory towers, it’s hard to know what discerns a true academic from an amateur.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "But one thing is certain, what's ever driving the internal narrative is what truly counts.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}